    <p><a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a></p>

    <h1>On so&#xAD;cial me&#xAD;dia</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <time datetime="2021-01-14"><a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20210114/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2021-01-14">2021-01-14</a></time> -
        PHOTOS: ADACHOI/WEIBO, MAXZHANG/WEIBO

            <a href="/category/tag-268449470/en/sg">Celebrities</a> &middot;            <a href="/category/tag-537068148/en/sg">Hong Kong</a> &middot;            <a href="/category/tag-538575333/en/sg">Ip Man</a> &middot;            <a href="/category/tag-540956486/en/sg">Master Z: The Ip Man Legacy</a>     </section>

        <p>AN­NIVER­SARY DANCE-OFF: Hong Kong ac­tress Ada Choi and ac­tor</p>
        <p>Max Zhang (both above) cel­e­brated their 13th wed­ding an­niver­sary on Tues­day with some funky dance moves (left). Dressed in match­ing black out­fits, they im­pro­vised groovy 1970s-in­spired dance steps be­fore fool­ing around by teas­ing each other. At one point, he pre­tended to kick her butt in the dance-off he posted on his Weibo ac­count.</p>
        <p>The 46-year-old Chi­nese ac­tor from Mas­ter Z: The Ip Man Le­gacy (2018) wrote: “Wed­ding an­niver­sary. Thir­teen years of weath­er­ing the storms to­gether. This is how we did it.” The cou­ple have two daugh­ters, aged nine and seven, and a son, one. They have largely stayed out of the public eye in the past year or so.</p>
        <p>Choi, 47, known for her roles in Armed Re­ac­tion III (2001) and Em­presses In The Palace (2011), also posted a heart­felt mes­sage on her ac­count: “Thir­teen years lace an­niver­sary. We have weath­ered the wind and rain, but have also taken in the scenery.” She added a sim­ple wish: “To live a healthy and peace­ful life, that is enough. May we cher­ish each other and walk to­gether as we learn more about love.”</p>

